ChatPrototype: A chat message viewer prototype. Work-in-progress for a
Quassel-like IRC GUI with detachable core.

Works best with Qt5. Works with Qt4. Please tell me about your experiences with
either.

First, update Git submodules:
  git submodule update --init

Build using cmake:
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake [options] ..
  make
  ./ChatPrototype

Recommend release build with assertions enabled, i.e. add to options:
  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo

To build with libc++ (e.g. Clang on Mac OS X), add to options:
  -DUSE_LIBCPP=YES
